               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office prayers and litanies (fols. 1ra-19vb)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse "Ordinary of the Mass" (fols. 19vb-45ra)
 I) Daily Office prayers
                     and litanies (fols. 45ra-49rb)
 III) Anaphoras (fols. 49rb-141vb )
                     III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fol. 49rb-61va)
 III-2) Anaphora of Our
                     Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 61va-65ra)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our Lady by St
                     Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 65ra-73vb)
 III-4) Anaphora of St John, son of
                     Thunder (fols. 73vb-82vb)
 III-5) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of
                     Nicaea (fols. 82ra-89ra)
 III-6) Anaphora of John of Constantinople (fols.
                     89ra-93vb)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus (fols.
                     93vb-99va)
 III-8) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 99va-104vb)
                     III-9) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols. 104vb-114ra)
 III-10)
                     Anaphora of St Dioscorus of Alexandria (fols.114ra-117ra)
 III-11) Anaphora
                     of St Gregory of Armenia ("Hosanna-liturgy of St Gregory") (fols.
                     114ra-123va)
 III-12) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols.
                     123va-130ra)
 III-13) Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fols.
                     130ra-138va)
 III-14) Second Anaphora of St Gregory ("Christmas-liturgy of
                     St Gregory") (fols. 138va-141vb)
 
 Additio 1.</summary>
